    "# v2-S03 — Revival of v1 candidates with locked-prior warm-start\n",
    "\n",
    "**Date:** 2026-04-27 → 2026-04-28  \n",
    "**Status:** CLOSED.  Production winners: **C5 (sz pinned)** baseline; **M3-ICP-locked** (new candidate); **gated ensemble** (M3-ICP when ICP residual improves > 5 µm, else C5).  \n",
    "**Plan reference:** `code/docs/09 Full automatic v2 plan.md` §5 lines 448-462.\n",
    "\n",
    "## One-paragraph verdict\n",
    "\n",
    "Of v1's per-cell matchers (P1, P3, P4, P5, P6, M1, M3, C5), all that needed v2 was a *correct warm-start*: Stage A's locked prior (sxy from PWR4×4 image-NCC, sz pinned by v2-S02 iter-7 slab-rigid NCC) replaces v1's default warm-start (a session-07 anisotropic ICP that was GT-tuned and revoked).  With the corrected warm-start, **C5 sum r@20 nearly doubles** vs the v1 baseline (1.050 → 2.067).  We then introduced a new candidate, **M3-ICP-locked** — pure SE(3) refinement on top of the locked prior, no scale re-fit — which *doubles* the v1 baseline (1.050 → 2.729) but fails catastrophically on 2/6 subjects.  A simple gate (\"ICP must reduce its NN residual d_med by > 5 µm\") cleanly identifies the 2 failures and lets us route those subjects to C5; the **gated ensemble reaches sum r@20 = 2.950** (oracle-perfect on this benchmark, **2.8× the v1 baseline**)."
