    "## 3. M3-ICP-locked: design and results\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why distinct from C5/P1/P4/P6?**  All four re-fit the full 7-DOF affine, which can drift away from the GT-validated sz pin.  M3-ICP-locked freezes the entire 7-DOF affine and refines *only* a residual `(R, t) ∈ SE(3)` by ICP on the warped CZ → HCR cloud.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Algorithm** (`bench_e_m3_icp_szpinned.py::m3_icp_pairs`):\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Warp CZ centroids by the locked prior with `sz_init = sz_peak_iter7`.\n",
    "2. Loop up to 10 iters:  \n",
    "   a. 1-NN match cz_warped → hcr_gfp via `cKDTree`.  \n",
    "   b. Robust inliers: `d_nn ≤ med(d_nn) + 3·MAD(d_nn)`.  \n",
    "   c. Procrustes rigid fit (no scale) on inlier pairs.  \n",
    "   d. Compose into `(R_resid, t_resid)`; convergence: `|Δt| < 0.5 µm` AND `|Δθ| < 0.2°`.\n",
    "3. Final NN pairs in 30-µm radius; `confidence = 1/(1 + d/σ_med)`; dedupe best-conf-per-hcr."
   ]
  },
